# MegaLinter build image - not a production container
DS-0002
DS-0026

# `lru` 0.15.0 is pulled in transitively by `walkers` 0.42.
# Walkers is pinned to 0.42 (see CLAUDE.md: highest version on egui 0.31;
# upgrading walkers requires upgrading egui, out of scope for this batch).
# Severity: LOW. Stacked-borrows invariant in IterMut; we don't call IterMut
# on the tile cache. Revisit when walkers/egui are bumped.
GHSA-rhfx-m35p-ff5j

# `thrift` 0.17.0 — no fixed upstream version published yet.
# Severity: MEDIUM. Pulled in via parquet/arrow stack.
# Memory allocation with excessive size value; only reachable when parsing
# untrusted Thrift payloads, which Octa does not accept directly (it reads
# Parquet via the arrow/parquet crates which use thrift for metadata, where
# the file's own metadata cap bounds the allocation). Revisit when the
# upstream advisory publishes a fixed crate version.
CVE-2026-43868
